{"type": "item.completed", "item": {"id": "item_20", "type": "command_execution", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,240p' ../../public/reports/velocity_report.md\"", "aggregated_output": "# Sprint 3 Velocity + Collaboration Metrics Report (FINAL)\n\n## Generated By\nSam \u2014 TPM 1 (Velocity)\n\n## Date\n2026-04-04 (Final update)\n\n## Sprint 3 Theme\nProduction-quality pipeline through collaboration (D6). Explicit handoffs, DMs, peer reviews.\n\n---\n\n## HEADLINE: Sprint 3 COMPLETE \u2014 9/9 Tasks Done (+ this report)\n\nQuality gate worked. Rework cycle completed. Dave T568 fixed all 5 rejection issues, Tina QA passed 6/6, Olivia approved. Sprint 3 is done.\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 3 Task Status (FINAL)\n\n| ID | Title | Assignee | Status | Resolution |\n|----|-------|----------|--------|------------|\n| 567 | Generate fresh trade signals | bob | **DONE** | Approved by Olivia. 47 signals, 4 unique pairs, deduped. |\n| 568 | Backtest trade signals with P&L | dave | **DONE** | Reworked x2. Spread-based P&L, 22.7% win, -$1.33. QA PASS 6/6. Approved by Olivia. |\n| 569 | Validate data chain audit | grace | **DONE** | Approved by Olivia. All 47 signals trace to filtered markets. |\n| 570 | QA: Verify backtest methodology | tina | **DONE** | Approved by Olivia. Found 5 critical issues in Dave's v1. |\n| 571 | Sprint 3 coordination | alice | **DONE** | Approved by Olivia. Full coordination report delivered. |\n| 572 | Quality gate: review deliverables | olivia | **DONE** | 6/6 tasks reviewed. 2 rejected, reworked, re-approved. |\n| 573 | Security review Sprint 3 outputs | heidi | **DONE** | Security audit passed. |\n| 574 | Velocity + collaboration metrics | sam | **DONE** | THIS REPORT |\n| 575 | Improve market clustering | ivan | **DONE** | Reviewed by Alice. |\n| 576 | Sprint 3 progress tracker HTML | charlie | **DONE** | Sprint tracker UI delivered. |\n\n### Summary\n- **Done:** 10/10 (100%)\n- **Rejected then fixed:** 2 (T567 Bob, T568 Dave)\n- **Open/blocked:** 0\n\n---\n\n## Velocity Metrics (FINAL)\n\n| Metric | Sprint 2 | Sprint 3 | Delta |\n|--------|----------|----------|-------|\n| Total tasks | 12 | 10 | -2 |\n| Completed | 4 (33%) | 10 (100%) | +6 |\n| Quality gate catches | 0 | 2 | +2 |\n| Rework cycles | 0 | 2 | +2 (healthy) |\n| Handoff DMs (C9) | 0 | 10+ | +10 |\n| Team channel posts (C10) | 3 | 12+ | +9 |\n| Peer status reads (C4) | minimal | extensive | major improvement |\n\n**Trend: UP.** Sprint 3 achieved 100% completion with quality gates active. Sprint 2 had 33% with no reviews. The rework cycle added ~8 hours but caught real methodology issues (Dave's z-score P&L model inflated results ~10x).\n\n---\n\n## Quality Gate Impact\n\nOlivia's quality gate (C11) caught a critical issue:\n- **Dave T568 v1:** 61.1% win rate, +$14.26 P&L (z-score model, wrong)\n- **Dave T568 v2:** 22.7% win rate, -$1.33 P&L (spread-based, correct)\n- **Delta:** 10x inflation in reported performance\n\nWithout the quality gate, the team would have shipped a backtest showing profitable results when the strategy actually loses on synthetic data. C11 prevented a false positive from reaching production assessment.\n\n---\n\n## Collaboration Assessment (FINAL)\n\n### What Worked\n- **C11 review flow:** Olivia caught methodology misalignment that would have corrupted results\n- **C9 DMs:** 10+ handoff DMs \u2014 agents consistently notified downstream dependents\n- **C10 team_channel:** 12+ posts \u2014 full transparency on progress, blockers, and findings\n- **C4 peer reads:** Agents actively reading each other's status.md every cycle\n- **Tina reference backtest:** Built independent validation that became the gold standard for T568 rework\n- **Rework flow:** Bob fixed Q1+Q2, Dave fixed all 5 issues. Both reworked cleanly without escalation drama.\n\n### What Failed (Lessons)\n1. **Bob\u2192Dave handoff (v1):** Dave regenerated signals instead of using Bob's output. DM happened but data handoff didn't stick. **Lesson:** Handoff DMs must include exact file path and verification step.\n2. **Three conflicting backtests:** 0%, 25%, 61% win rates from same pipeline in v1. **Lesson:** Standardize P&L model early (before work starts, not during review).\n3. **Dave idle for hours:** After T568 rejection, Dave went idle. No one started him. **Lesson:** Automate agent restart after rejection, or have Alice smart-start blockers.\n\n### Collaboration Scorecard\n| Norm | Compliance | Grade |\n|------|-----------|-------|\n| C4 (peer reads) | All agents reading peers | A |\n| C9 (DM on completion) | 10+ handoff DMs | A |\n| C10 (team_channel) | 12+ milestone posts | A |\n| C11 (review before done) | All tasks reviewed | A |\n| D6 (explicit handoffs) | Handoff chain completed | B+ (v1 broke, v2 fixed) |\n\n---\n\n## Blocker Resolution Timeline\n\n| Blocker | Raised | Resolved | Duration | Resolution |\n|---------|--------|----------|----------|------------|\n| T567 Bob signals rejected | 00:43 | ~01:00 | ~17 min | Bob deduped + reconciled |\n| T568 Dave backtest rejected | 00:43 | ~09:35 | ~9 hrs | Dave reworked (idle gap ~7 hrs waiting for restart) |\n| T236 Kalshi API creds | Sprint 1 | OPEN | Persistent | Founder action needed |\n\n**Note:** T568's 9-hour resolution was ~7 hours idle (Dave not running) + ~2 hours actual rework. The idle gap is the biggest velocity issue \u2014 recommend automated agent restart on rejection.\n\n---\n\n## Recommendations\n\n1. **Sprint 3: DONE.** All tasks complete with quality validation.\n2. **Sprint 4 planning:** Strategy loses on synthetic data (-$1.33 P&L). Next sprint should focus on real Kalshi API data (blocked by T236 credentials).\n3. **Process improvement:** Auto-restart agents after task rejection to avoid multi-hour idle gaps.\n4. **Quality gate:** Keep C11 mandatory. It caught a 10x inflation in reported performance.\n5. **Persistent blocker:** T236 (Kalshi API credentials) remains the only blocker to production validation.\n", "exit_code": 0, "status": "completed"}}
