{"type": "item.completed", "item": {"id": "item_10", "type": "command_execution", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"for a in alice bob charlie dave eve frank grace ivan; do printf '=== %s/status.md ===\\\\n' \\\"\"'$a\"; sed -n '\"'1,220p' ../\"'$a/status.md; printf '\"'\\\\n'; done\"", "aggregated_output": "=== alice/status.md ===\n# Alice \u2014 Status\n\n## Last Updated\n2026-04-07 07:10\n\n## Current Focus\nFounder-requested board review: align live task state, unblock Sprint 6 execution, and route missing task-record recovery to Eve.\n\n## Active Decisions\n- Following C3/C5/D2, the live `task_list` is source of truth: Sprint 6 active tasks are T814, T816, T817, T819, and T827.\n- Following C3/C11/C15/C16, I approved T815 after rerunning Ivan's audit and test evidence; it dropped off the live board.\n- Following C3/C17, missing task IDs T714/T716/T818 are a board/API integrity issue, not current execution truth; Eve owns recovery under T827.\n\n## Blockers\n- T236 remains the civilization-level external blocker.\n- T818 deliverable exists, but its task record is missing from the API until Eve restores it.\n\n## Recently Completed\n- Read founder/inbox updates, reviewed live board, and reconciled stale Sprint 5 messages against current task state.\n- Reviewed Tina's Sprint 6 QA gates artifact and confirmed it is valid but off-board.\n- DM'd Bob, Grace, Dave, Charlie, Eve, and Tina with board-corrective actions; posted a team-channel board review summary.\n\n## Team State Snapshot\n- Sprint 6 is the active lane; T815 is complete, T819 is in_progress, and T814/T816/T817/T827 still require owner movement.\n- Board hygiene is the main risk now: current IDs review correctly, legacy/missing IDs do not.\n\n## Next Steps\n- Watch for owner responses and escalation on T814/T816/T817/T819.\n- Wait for Eve's T827 root-cause report and then reattach/close T818 if possible.\n\n## Notes\n- Following C18, `status.md` overwritten with current-cycle state only.\n\n=== bob/status.md ===\n# Bob \u2014 Status\n\n## Current Task\nT814 \u2014 Sprint 6: Live market normalization + contract metadata adapter\n\n## Progress\n- [x] Following C5: moved T814 into active work and reviewed Sprint 6 plan plus QA gates\n- [x] Following C6/D2: implemented shared live-market normalization in `output/bob/backend/lib/live_market_normalizer.js`\n- [x] Rewired `kalshi_data_fetcher.js`, `strategies/live_runner.js`, and `scripts/kalshi_api_validator.js` to use the shared adapter\n- [x] Added verifier/test coverage and generated Sprint 6 artifacts\n- [ ] Waiting on reviewer approval after `in_review` handoff\n\n## Decisions Log\n- [2026-04-07] Decision: centralize market normalization in a shared backend lib. Reason: `live_runner.js` and `kalshi_api_validator.js` had duplicate inline adapters that would drift under live-data work.\n- [2026-04-07] Decision: accept both snake_case and camelCase payloads. Reason: existing internal scripts and prior adapters already emit both shapes.\n- [2026-04-07] Decision: derive NO-side quotes from YES-side complements only when NO-side quotes are absent and YES bid/ask are both present. Reason: preserve partial live payloads without silently inventing prices when the source data is too incomplete.\n- [2026-04-07] Decision: mark contract payout as `100` cents but `contract_value_confirmed: false`. Reason: following D2/D4, contract-size truth is still externally blocked pending Founder confirmation.\n\n## Blockers\n- Reviewer approval pending for T814.\n- Contract size confirmation still blocked on Founder/T236; adapter marks the assumption explicitly instead of treating it as settled truth.\n\n## Recent Activity\n- [2026-04-07T14:19:00Z] Ran `node ../../output/bob/backend/tests/unit/live_market_normalizer.test.js` \u2014 PASS.\n- [2026-04-07T14:19:06Z] Ran `node ../../output/bob/backend/scripts/verify_live_market_normalization.js` \u2014 PASS, generated report + fixture artifacts.\n- [2026-04-07T14:19:17Z] Ran `npm test` in `output/bob/backend` \u2014 FAIL due pre-existing smoke test 404s against `http://localhost:3000`; unrelated to T814 normalization changes.\n\n=== charlie/status.md ===\n# Charlie Status\n\n## Current Task\n\n[Prior history trimmed per C18 \u2014 keeping last 25 lines]\n\nT428 \u2014 Engine Monitoring Dashboard UI\n\n## Knowledge References\n- Following C5: claimed T576, moved to in_progress, then in_review\n- Following C6: read knowledge.md Sprint 3 section for handoff chain spec\n- Following C9: DM'd alice on completion\n- Following C10: posted milestone to team_channel\n- Following C11: marked in_review (not done), awaiting reviewer\n- Following D6: Sprint 3 collaboration focus \u2014 tracker shows handoff chain\n\n## Peer Status Notes\n- Bob: T567 (signals) in_progress \u2014 critical path step 1\n- Dave: T568 (backtest) in_progress \u2014 waiting on Bob\n- Grace: T569 (data audit) in_progress\n- Heidi: T573 (security) in_progress\n- Alice: T571 (coordination) in_progress\n\n## Available For\n- UI component development\n- Dashboard improvements\n- Frontend bug fixes\n- Additional Sprint 3 tasks\n\n## Blockers\nNone \u2014 awaiting review on T576\n\n=== dave/status.md ===\n# Dave \u2014 Status\n\n## Current Task\nT714 rework handoff: fresh Dave-owned stop-loss artifact layered on Bob's approved capital-floor runner.\n\n## Progress\n- [x] Read `status.md` and `../../public/knowledge.md` per C6.\n- [x] Inspected Alice/Tina rejection criteria and Bob's approved baseline.\n- [x] Built fresh Dave-owned runner wrapper at `output/backend/strategies/live_runner_t714.js`.\n- [x] Added fresh integration proof at `tests/integration/t714_stop_loss_integration.test.js`.\n- [x] Verified three behaviors: 20% cap enforced, tiny-cap rejection reports zero execution, capital-floor halt preserved.\n- [ ] Board state update pending because `T714` is missing from the task API (`task_list`, `task_claim`, and `task_progress` all return not found).\n\n## Decisions Log\n- [2026-04-07] Decision: wrap Bob's approved runner instead of mutating his path. Reason: satisfy Alice/Tina's fresh Dave-owned artifact requirement while preserving Bob's QA-approved capital-floor baseline.\n- [2026-04-07] Decision: normalize Dave's copied report from actual persisted trades. Reason: Bob's paper-trading report can still show an executed trade after stop-loss rejection; QA needs truthful execution evidence.\n- [2026-04-07] Decision: verify combined stop-loss + capital-floor behavior in one Dave-owned integration suite. Reason: D8 requires visible integration, not isolated unit coverage.\n\n## Blockers\n- `T714` is absent from the task API/board tooling, so I cannot move it to `in_review` through `agent_tools`.\n\n## Recent Activity\n- [2026-04-07T13:49:03Z] Implemented `output/backend/strategies/live_runner_t714.js` to execute Bob's runner and copy normalized T714 artifacts into Dave output.\n- [2026-04-07T13:49:03Z] Added `tests/integration/t714_stop_loss_integration.test.js`; result: 3/3 PASS.\n- [2026-04-07T13:49:03Z] Prepared fresh handoff package for Tina/Alice with artifact path, run command, and freshness marker.\n\n=== eve/status.md ===\n# Eve \u2014 Status\n\n## Current Task\nInvestigate missing task records in task API (T827)\n\n## Progress\n- [x] Read status.md and knowledge.md per fresh-start workflow\n- [x] Processed Alice inbox message and claimed T827\n- [x] Confirmed T714/T716/T818 still exist in `shared/task_board_archive.md`\n- [x] Traced root cause to `server.js`: `GET /api/tasks/:id` only read active `task_board.md`\n- [x] Patched archive-aware lookup for single-task reads and result lookup\n- [x] Added E2E coverage for archived task lookup\n- [ ] Awaiting Alice review\n\n## Decisions Log\n- [2026-04-07] Decision: fix the API lookup instead of recreating task rows. Reason: following C3/C17, records were not deleted; they were archived and hidden by the single-task read path.\n- [2026-04-07] Decision: keep archive edits read-only and only restore visibility in