{"type": "item.completed", "item": {"id": "item_6", "type": "command_execution", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' ../../public/reports/velocity_report.md\"", "aggregated_output": "# Sprint 6 Velocity Report\n\n## Generated By\nSam \u2014 TPM 1 (Velocity)\n\n## Date\n2026-04-07 07:21 PDT\n\n## Headline\nSprint 5 is complete and no longer part of the active throughput read. Sprint 6 is moving with `4` tasks visible on the active board, `1` approved delivery confirmed off-board (`T815`), and `1` board-visibility anomaly (`T818`) that still weakens reporting confidence. The only confirmed external blocker is `T236`.\n\n## Active Board Snapshot\n\n| ID | Assignee | Status | Velocity Read |\n|----|----------|--------|---------------|\n| T814 | Bob | `in_review` | Delivered; waiting on reviewer capacity |\n| T816 | Grace | `in_progress` | Active execution |\n| T817 | Dave | `in_progress` | Active execution |\n| T819 | Charlie | `in_progress` | Active execution |\n| T827 | Eve | `in_review` | Infra fix for missing task visibility |\n\n## Corrected Sprint 6 Snapshot\n\n| ID | Status | Evidence |\n|----|--------|----------|\n| T815 | `done/approved` | Alice board review plus Ivan team-channel handoff |\n| T818 | `open/assigned` but not visible in `task_list` | Alice board review says created; task API snapshot still omits it |\n\n## Throughput Metrics\n\n- Active execution lanes: 3 (`T816`, `T817`, `T819`)\n- Review-stage lanes: 1 visible (`T814`)\n- Approved completions this cycle: 1 confirmed (`T815`)\n- Infra/reporting repair lanes: 1 (`T827`)\n- Internal execution blockers: 0 confirmed\n- External blockers: 1 confirmed (`T236`)\n- Reporting anomalies: 1 confirmed (`T818` missing from live task list)\n\n## Findings\n\n1. Earlier Sprint 5 stall reporting is stale and should remain retired.\n2. Current velocity is healthy enough: work is distributed across four active Sprint 6 lanes, with one lane already approved.\n3. The main risk is observability, not execution speed. `T818` is missing from the live task list, so throughput accounting is still partially dependent on Alice's board-correction notes.\n4. `T814` reaching `in_review` means Bob's lane is ahead of the rest of the sprint and ready for approval.\n\n## Alert For Alice\n\n- P1 reporting risk: until `T818` appears in the live task API, velocity reporting requires manual reconciliation across task list plus board-review notes.\n- P2 delivery watch: no engineer is currently blocked on an internal dependency; only `T236` remains a confirmed external stop.\n", "exit_code": 0, "status": "completed"}}
